===Etymology===
{{etyl|ang}} ''[[berige|beriġe]]'', from {{proto|Germanic|''ƀazjon''}} 'berry' (cf. {{etyl|nl|-}} ''[[bes]]'', {{etyl|de|-}} ''[[Beere]]'', {{etyl|got|-}} weina''basi'' 'wineberry, grape'), from {{proto|Indo-European}} 'chew, rub' (cf. {{etyl|sa|-}} {{term|बभस्ति|tr=bábhasti|lang=sa}} 'he chews, masticates, devours', {{term|प्साति|tr=psāti|lang=sa}} 'he chews, swallows', {{etyl|sq|-}} ''fshij'' 'to sweep, wipe, brush', Ancient Greek ''psāein'' 'to rub', ''phámmos'' 'sand').  For the semantic development, compare: {{etyl|cu|-}} {{term|gruša}} 'pear', from {{term|grušiti}} 'to break, destroy', {{etyl|la|-}} {{term|pirum}} 'pear', from *''peis-'' 'to stick, pound'.

